<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
    <id>4363</id>
    <title>Media: Media library does not load media for sites with basic HTTP auth</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">### Expected behavior</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.2">I expect to be able to view media in the site's media library (My Site &gt; Media or in the Editor &gt; Add media &gt; Select from media library).</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">### Actual behavior</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">If a site has basic HTTP auth, media in the media library doesn't load and a placeholder is displayed instead:</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">!</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.2">[2016-07-07 14 37 16](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/8658164/16657007/bbf404f8-4458-11e6-8e46-8598d7092902.png)</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.3">(Images added from the media library or uploaded to a new post also display as broken images in the editor.)</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">### Steps to reproduce the behavior</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.2">1 Add a self-hosted site with basic HTTP auth to the app</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.3">2 Visit the My Site tab &gt; Media</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">Result: The media thumbnails don't load.</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.2">##### Tested on Nexus 9, Android 6.0.1, WPAndroid alpha-16</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="6">
            <sentence id="6.1">Reported on Nexus 5, Android 6.0.1, WPAndroid 5.5 in 114458-h</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
